cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with statistical machine translation models and improving translation quality. It also involves the use of neural networks for learning sentence semantic representations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a feed-forward neural network for translation prediction, which is related to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's focus on improving translation quality through the use of global sentence-level information suggests a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
